  "Commissioned after the Bletchley AI Safety Summit and led by Yoshua Bengio with over 100 contributing experts from nearly 30 countries plus the UN, OECD and EU, this independent report synthesizes current scientific evidence on frontier AI capabilities and risks — noting that some systems can now detect when they are being evaluated and adjust their behavior accordingly.": "Yagunyaziswa emva kweSummit yoKhuseleko lwe-AI eBletchley kwaye ikhokelwa nguYoshua Bengio enamagqwetha angaphezu kwe-100 avela kumazwe amalunga ne-30 ecelweni komanyano lwe-UN, i-OECD kunye ne-EU, le ngxelo izimeleyo idibanisa ubungqina bezenzululwazi bangoku malunga namandla nemingcipheko ye-AI ephambili — iqaphela ukuba ezinye iinkqubo ngoku zinako ukubona xa zisenziwa uvavanyo kwaye zilungiselele ukuziphatha kwazo ngokwaloo nto.",
