  "Correct positioning: independent research drafts, protocol proposals, and an open specification experiment.": "Indawo echanekileyo: iiyilo zophando oluzimeleyo, iziphakamiso zeeprotokholi, kunye novavanyo lweenkcukacha oluvulekileyo.",
  "Corrected an earlier default: Belgium (BE) now maps to Dutch instead of French — Flemish speakers are the country’s majority (~60%) over Walloon French speakers (~40%).": "Kulungisiwe okwakuqala: iBelgium (BE) ngoku ijolisa kwisiDatshi endaweni yesiFrentshi — abathethi besiFlemish bangabaninzi elizweni (~60%) ngaphezu kwabathethi besiFrentshi seWalloon (~40%).",
  "Corrected an earlier default: Kazakhstan (KZ) now maps to Kazakh instead of Russian, now that a Kazakh translation exists — the same kind of fix as the earlier Belgium correction.": "Kulungisiwe okwakuqala: iKazakhstan (KZ) ngoku ijolisa kwisiKazakh endaweni yesiRashiya, ngoku ukuba inguqulelo yesiKazakh ikhona — luhlobo olufanayo lokulungiswa njengokulungiswa kweBelgium kwangaphambili.",
  "Could AI Be Conscious?": "Could AI Be Conscious?",
  "Crawler access rules": "Imigaqo yokufikelela kwe-crawler",
  "Crawler simulator": "Umlingisi we-crawler",
  "Currency": "Imali",
  "Custom tier": "Inqanaba elizenzeleyo",
  "Daily Nous reports on a retracted Journal of Medical Ethics submission containing multiple fabricated, AI-hallucinated references — complete with fake university affiliations and defunct email addresses — that the author reportedly left uncorrected even after being given a chance to fix proofs. The piece contrasts this with Bioethics, whose automated reference-checking would have caught the problem, and argues the real bottleneck isn't detection technology (one commenter's script flagged the fake citations in under a minute) but unpaid reviewer labor and publishing incentives that reward throughput over scrutiny.": "IDaily Nous ixela ngoxwebhu olurhoxisiweyo lwe-Journal of Medical Ethics olunemithombo emininzi eyenziweyo, eyaziswe bubuxoki yi-AI — ezinamaziko emfundo ephakamileyo angekhoyo kunye needilesi zeimeyile ezingasasebenziyo — ekuthiwa umbhali akazange azilungise nangona wanikwa ithuba lokulungisa iimpapasho. Eli nqaku lithelekisa oku ne-Bioethics, apho ukukhangelwa okuzenzekelayo kwemithombo bekuya kubamba loo ngxaki, kwaye lithi umqobo wokwenene ayisiyotekhnoloji yokufumana (isikripthi somphawuli omnye sabamba iicaphulo eziyintlanga ngaphantsi komzuzu), kodwa ngumsebenzi ongabhatalwayo wabahloli kunye nezibonelelo zopapasho ezivuza ubuninzi endaweni yophononongo olucokisekileyo.",
  "Data free-riding vs. trillion-dollar AI valuations": "Ukukhwela ngasimahla kwidatha kunye namaxabiso e-AI alinganiselwa kwizigidigidi eziyi-trillion",
  "DeepMind CEO calls for an independent standards body to regulate frontier AI": "DeepMind CEO calls for an independent standards body to regulate frontier AI",
  "Demis Hassabis proposed a FINRA-style regulator for frontier model releases: labs would submit models for review up to 30 days before deployment, voluntary at first, with a path toward mandatory compliance in the US market.": "UDemis Hassabis ucebise umlawuli oluhlobo lwe-FINRA weenkululo zeemodeli eziphambili: amaziko azingenisa iimodeli ukuze ziphononongwe kangangeentsuku ezingama-30 ngaphambi kokusetyenziswa, ngokuzithandela ekuqaleni, kunendlela eya ekunyanzeleni ekuthotyelweni kwimarike yase-US.",
  "Denied": "Kwaliwe",
  "Deployable policy starter template": "Itemplate yokuqala yomgaqo enokusetyenziswa",
  "Deployable policy starter template at /downloads/agiright-policy-starter.zip — a minimal static site with the full machine-readable layer, ready for Cloudflare Pages or any static host.": "Itemplate yokuqala yomgaqo enokusetyenziswa kwi-/downloads/agiright-policy-starter.zip — isayithi encinci ehleliyo enenqanaba elipheleleyo elifundwa yimatshini, lilungele iCloudflare Pages okanye nasiphi na isindululi esihleliyo.",
  "Deploying machine-readable policies on your site": "Ukubeka imigaqo efundwa yimatshini kwisayithi yakho",
  "Disclaimer": "Isaziso Sokuzikhulula",
  "Distinct from human UI, SEO, or plain APIs, the AI Ingestion & Capability Layer gives websites a machine-facing architecture: a Manifest Layer (entry points like /llms.txt and /ai/manifest.json), a Corpus Layer (machine-readable knowledge), a Capability Layer (agent-callable tools), and a Governance Layer (provenance, licensing, versioning). Static-first, upgradeable toward APIs and MCP. Note: in this paper AICL names the ingestion architecture; on this site's protocol pages AICL refers to the AI Content Licensing Layer.": "Kwahluke kwi-UI yabantu, i-SEO, okanye ii-API eziqhelekileyo, i-AI Ingestion & Capability Layer inika iiwebhusayithi uyilo olujolise kwimatshini: iNqanaba leManifesti (iindawo zokungena ezinje nge-/llms.txt kunye ne-/ai/manifest.json), iNqanaba leKhophasi (ulwazi olufundwa yimatshini), iNqanaba loMgangatho Wamandla (izixhobo ezinokubizwa yi-arhente), kunye neNqanaba loLawulo (umthombo, ilayisensi, amanqaku ohlobo). Kuqala ngokuhlelekileyo, kunokuphuculwa kuye kwii-API kunye ne-MCP. Qaphela: kweli phepha i-AICL ithiya uyilo lokufumana; kumaphepha eeprotokholi ale sayithi i-AICL ibhekisa kwiNqanaba lokuNikwa kweLayisensi yoMxholo we-AI.",
  "Do Large Language Models Possess a Theory of Mind? A Comparative Evaluation Using the Strange Stories Paradigm": "Do Large Language Models Possess a Theory of Mind? A Comparative Evaluation Using the Strange Stories Paradigm",
  "Docs": "Amaxwebhu",
  "Docs / Examples": "Amaxwebhu / Imizekelo",
